{
  "findings": [
    {
      "title": "[P1] Keep preset-init flag instance-scoped",
      "body": "The new `areDefaultPresetsInitialized` flag is module-level state, so once one `Amounts` instance sets it to `true`, later mounts in the same SPA session skip the initialization effect entirely. This causes incorrect initial UI mode (for example, opening another action page with frequency-specific presets can still default to apply-all) because the component no longer derives state from that page’s form data.",
      "confidence_score": 0.95,
      "priority": 1,
      "code_location": {
        "absolute_file_path": "/Users/duhl/git/anedot-frontend/src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/Designer/Finance/Amounts/Amounts.tsx",
        "line_range": {
          "start": 35,
          "end": 35
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "[P1] Handle unequal preset array lengths safely",
      "body": "`presetsMatch` assumes both arrays have the same length and dereferences `b[index].amount` unconditionally. If one frequency has presets and another has an empty array (a reachable state after clearing one frequency), the initialization check calls this function and throws on `undefined.amount`, breaking render for the amounts panel.",
      "confidence_score": 0.96,
      "priority": 1,
      "code_location": {
        "absolute_file_path": "/Users/duhl/git/anedot-frontend/src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/Designer/Finance/Amounts/Amounts.tsx",
        "line_range": {
          "start": 29,
          "end": 30
        }
      }
    },
    {
      "title": "[P2] Prevent switching to per-frequency mode without options",
      "body": "The switch allows turning off “apply to all” even when there are no recurring frequencies (`presetFrequencyOptions.length === 0`). In that state, `activeFrequency` becomes `undefined`, the preset editor disappears, and users are shown an “Enable presets” action despite existing default presets, which is an invalid and confusing mode for one-time-only configurations.",
      "confidence_score": 0.86,
      "priority": 2,
      "code_location": {
        "absolute_file_path": "/Users/duhl/git/anedot-frontend/src/pages/ActionPages/pages/ActionPagesBuilder/Designer/Finance/Amounts/Amounts.tsx",
        "line_range": {
          "start": 81,
          "end": 85
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "overall_correctness": "patch is incorrect",
  "overall_explanation": "The patch introduces shared module state and unsafe preset comparison logic that can produce incorrect initialization or runtime crashes in realistic editing flows. It also permits an invalid UI mode when no recurring frequencies exist.",
  "overall_confidence_score": 0.93
}

